# modelguild/models.policy — committed default policy for models used by
# /guild:consult, /guild:panel, /guild:workshop, /guild:review,
# /guild:research, /guild:delegate, and /guild:collaborate.
#
# Format:  <tier>  <glob-pattern>        # optional comment
#   tier    = deny | ask | allow
#   pattern = a shell glob matched against the FULL provider/model id
#             (e.g. openai/gpt-5.6-sol, opencode/deepseek-v4-flash-free)
#
# FIRST MATCH WINS, top to bottom. Put specific rules above broad ones.
#   deny   — the guild tools hard-refuse to run this model (the call returns isError).
#   ask    — Claude must confirm with you before using it (the tool call carries
#            confirmed:true, which Claude sets only after you approve).
#   allow  — use freely.
#
# Ships permissive (default-allow). Uncomment / edit to gate what YOU care about,
# or run `/guild:configure` for guided setup. Effective resolution is
# $GUILD_POLICY when set, otherwise a ruleful git-ignored
# modelguild/models.policy.local, otherwise THIS shared/committed default. An empty or
# comment-only local file does not override this file.
# Note: a call with no explicit model uses opencode's default model, whose id isn't
# known here, so it can't be policed — pass a model to bring it under policy.
#
# Examples (delete the leading '# ' to activate):
#   deny   *-sol*             # never use any Sol variant
#   ask    *fable*            # confirm before using Fable
#   ask    openai/gpt-5.6-*   # confirm before this whole family
#   allow  opencode/*         # free tier is always fine

allow  *                      # default: everything is allowed
